<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{koso}}}} is a particle that emphasises the word, phrase or clause before it.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kore @EM{{koso}}@KJ{{ego^noma}}ga @KJ{{grope}}shi @KJ{{request}}meteitamonoda.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      This is the very thing we've been looking for.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
The idiomatic expression @HI{{kochira}} @EM{{@HI{{koso}}}} means "not at all, the pleasure is all mine".

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      A:　@HI{{doumoarigatougozaimashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      B:　@HI{{kochira koso.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      A:　Thank you very much.
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      B:　Not at all; the pleasure is all mine.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

